libfont-afm-perl (1.20-3) unstable; urgency=medium

  [ Salvatore Bonaccorso ]
  * Update Vcs-* headers for switch to salsa.debian.org

  [ Debian Janitor ]
  * Bump debhelper from old 9 to 12.
  * Set debhelper-compat version in Build-Depends.

  [ gregor herrmann ]
  * debian/watch: use uscan version 4.
  * Add fonts-urw-base35 to Build-Depends-Indep in order to enable a test.
  * Add a patch from Gentoo that allows us to override a font in a test.
    Thanks to Kent Fredric for the pointer on IRC.
  * debian/rules: set font to be used in t/afm.t.
  * Set font parameters for autopkgtest as well.
  * Update years of packaging copyright.
  * Declare compliance with Debian Policy 4.5.0.
  * Set Rules-Requires-Root: no.
  * Annotate test-only build dependencies with <!nocheck>.
  * Bump debhelper-compat to 13.
  * Tweak package description.

